.TH BURLS 1 "2026-04-23" "smartmet-monitor" "SmartMet Server"
.SH NAME
burls \- top URLs in a SmartMet access log
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B burls
.RI [ \-n\  N ]
.RI [ \-s\  reqs|ms|kb|mb ]
.RI [ LOG-FILE ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B burls
groups access\-log entries by URL path (query string stripped), then
prints the top
.B N
URLs sorted by the chosen metric. Each row shows request count, mean
latency, mean response size, total bandwidth in MB, and a horizontal
bar scaled to the row\-leading metric.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BI \-n \ N
Number of URLs to show. Default
.BR 20 .
.TP
.BI \-s \ SORT
Sort column. One of
.BR reqs ,\  ms ,\  kb ,\  mb :
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
.B reqs \- by request count
.IP \(bu 2
.B ms   \- by total time spent (ms)
.IP \(bu 2
.B kb   \- by mean response size (KB)
.IP \(bu 2
.B mb   \- by total bandwidth (MB)
.RE
Default
.BR ms .
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR bstat (1),
.BR bchart (1),
.BR bstatus (1),
.BR bkeys (1),
.BR smtop (1)
